subSubSection.paragraph:
Unmounted specimens.
Live adult female (
Fig. 1B
) body highly convex, truncated dorsally, yellowish to light brown in colour; with a white longitudinal stripe with irregular black border that is composed of pigments (which disappear during slide-mounting processes) running longitudinally from head to area anterior to anal plates on mid dorsum (
Fig. 1
); with some small, raised, irregularly-rounded black spots on the dorsum of unmounted specimens. Part of body margin covered by a thin layer of white wax, with ventral and upper part of body devoid of wax, at least on young females. All specimens were found on the stems of the host plant.

